{{page-title 'Theming'}}
<div class='w-full h-full p-5 flex flex-row justify-start items-start'>
	<MdcCard class='w-full max-w-full max-h-full'>
		<:header as |Header|>
			<Header class='flex flex-row justify-between items-center border-b'>
				<:headline as |Headline|>
					<Headline @text='THEMING' />
				</:headline>
				<:subheadline as |SubHeadline|>
					<SubHeadline @text='Changing colors and fonts at runtime' />
				</:subheadline>
			</Header>
		</:header>
		<:content as |Content|>
			<Content class='overflow-y-auto'>
				<article class='twyr-prose'>
					<h4 class='prose max-w-none'>Build-time Theming</h4>
					<p class='twyr-prose'>
						Build-time theming configuration is controlled by the
						entries in the
						<code>&lt;ember_app_name&gt;/app/styles/app.scss</code>
						file:
					</p>
					{{! prettier-ignore }}
					<pre class='twyr-prose mt-0'>
@use "sass:string";

/*
 * Material Design Components for the Web
 */

@use '@twyr/ember-mdc-web/dist/styles/ember-mdc-web' with (
	$primary-colour: &lt;primary_color_rgb&gt;,
	$secondary-colour: &lt;secondary_color_rgb&gt;,
	$error-colour: &lt;error_color_rgb&gt;,
	$surface-colour: &lt;surface_color_rgb&gt;,
	$background-colour: &lt;background_color_rgb&gt;,

	$body-font-family: string.unquote('&lt;body_font_name&gt;,sans-serif'),
	$header-font-family: string.unquote('&lt;headings_font_name&gt;, sans-serif')
);</pre>
					<p class='twyr-prose'>
						This configuration generates the CSS variables, etc.
						that get embedded in
						<code class='prose'>vendor.css</code>
						and used on the first render of the Ember App
					</p>

					<h4 class='prose max-w-none'>Global Run-time Theming</h4>
					<p class='twyr-prose'>
						Global run-time theming refers to changing the primary,
						secondary, and error, colours at run-time, and fonts,
						font-weights, font-sizes, etc. The values of these css
						properties can be changed by setting the values of the
						css variables on the
						<code class='twyr-prose'>root</code>
						element. The table below lists the more common
						properties:
					</p>
					<table class='prose max-w-none'>
						<thead class='twyr-prose'>
							<tr class='twyr-prose'>
								<th class='twyr-prose'>Colour CSS Variable</th>
								<th class='twyr-prose'>Application</th>
							</tr>
						</thead>
						<tbody class='twyr-prose'>
							<tr class='twyr-prose'>
								<td class='twyr-prose'><code
										class='twyr-prose'
									>--mdc-theme-primary</code></td>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>Get / set the primary
									theme colour</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class='twyr-prose'>
								<td class='twyr-prose'><code
										class='twyr-prose'
									>--mdc-theme-on-primary</code></td>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>Get / set the colour of
									the text against a primary colour background</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class='twyr-prose'>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>&nbsp;</td>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>&nbsp;</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class='twyr-prose'>
								<td class='twyr-prose'><code
										class='twyr-prose'
									>--mdc-theme-secondary</code></td>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>Get / set the secondary
									theme colour</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class='twyr-prose'>
								<td class='twyr-prose'><code
										class='twyr-prose'
									>--mdc-theme-on-secondary</code></td>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>Get / set the colour of
									the text against a secondary colour
									background</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class='twyr-prose'>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>&nbsp;</td>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>&nbsp;</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class='twyr-prose'>
								<td class='twyr-prose'><code
										class='twyr-prose'
									>--mdc-theme-error</code></td>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>Get / set the error theme
									colour</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class='twyr-prose'>
								<td class='twyr-prose'><code
										class='twyr-prose'
									>--mdc-theme-on-error</code></td>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>Get / set the colour of
									the text against an error colour background</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class='twyr-prose'>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>&nbsp;</td>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>&nbsp;</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class='twyr-prose'>
								<td class='twyr-prose'><code
										class='twyr-prose'
									>--mdc-theme-surface</code></td>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>Get / set the surface
									theme colour</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class='twyr-prose'>
								<td class='twyr-prose'><code
										class='twyr-prose'
									>--mdc-theme-on-surface</code></td>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>Get / set the colour of
									the text against a surface colour background</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class='twyr-prose'>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>&nbsp;</td>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>&nbsp;</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class='twyr-prose'>
								<td class='twyr-prose'><code
										class='twyr-prose'
									>--mdc-theme-background</code></td>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>Get / set the background
									theme colour</td>
							</tr>
						</tbody>
					</table>
					<table class='prose max-w-none'>
						<thead class='twyr-prose'>
							<tr class='twyr-prose'>
								<th class='twyr-prose'>Typography CSS Variable</th>
								<th class='twyr-prose'>Application</th>
							</tr>
						</thead>
						<tbody class='twyr-prose'>
							<tr class='twyr-prose'>
								<td class='twyr-prose'><code
										class='twyr-prose'
									>--mdc-typography-font-family</code></td>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>Get / set the font used
									across the board, when not overridden by a
									more specific directive</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class='twyr-prose'>
								<td class='twyr-prose'><code
										class='twyr-prose'
									>--mdc-typography-headline[1-6]-font-family</code></td>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>Get / set the font used
									by the headings h1, h2, etc.</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class='twyr-prose'>
								<td class='twyr-prose'><code
										class='twyr-prose'
									>--mdc-typography-subtitle[1-2]-font-family</code></td>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>Get / set the font used
									by the subtitles</td>
							</tr>
							<tr class='twyr-prose'>
								<td class='twyr-prose'><code
										class='twyr-prose'
									>--mdc-typography-body[1-2]-font-family</code></td>
								<td class='twyr-prose'>Get / set the font used
									in the body of an element</td>
							</tr>
						</tbody>
					</table>
					<p class='twyr-prose'>
						A comprehensive list of the CSS variables that can be
						set to customize the look and feel of the design system
						can be found at the
						<a
							class='twyr-prose'
							href='https://material.io/develop/web/theming/theming-guide'
							target='_blank'
							rel='noopener noreferrer'
						>MDC Web Theming Guide</a>
					</p>

					<h4 class='prose max-w-none'>Local Run-time Theming</h4>
					<p class='twyr-prose'>
						Local theming refers to the ability to change the theme
						for a particular element. For example, an input element
						may need to be marked as
						<code class='twyr-prose'>error</code>
						if the user input fails a validation test.
					</p>
					<p class='prose max-w-none'>
						To enable this functionalty, all EMDC Web components
						accept a
						<code class='twyr-prose'>@palette</code>
						argument. This argument takes either
						<code class='twyr-prose'>primary</code>, or
						<code class='twyr-prose'>secondary</code>, or
						<code class='twyr-prose'>error</code>, as acceptable
						values. When this argument is passed to the component,
						the theme for that element [NOT DESCENDANTS] is changed
						to reflect the correct colour scheme. The component
						demos provide examples of this functionality.
					</p>
				</article>
			</Content>
		</:content>
	</MdcCard>
</div>